import re
t = int(input())
special_char = re.compile('[@_!#$%^&*()<>?/\\|}{~:]')
for i in range(t):
    a = input()
    a = a.strip()
    n = len(a)
    if a[0] == '<' and a[1] == '/' and (a[n - 1] == '>') and (n > 3):
        ans = 'Success'
        b = a.replace(a[0], 'a')
        c = b.replace(a[1], 'a')
        d = c.replace(a[n - 1], 'a')
        for j in range(n):
            if d[j] != d[j].lower():
                ans = 'Error'
                break
            if special_char.search(d) != None:
                ans = 'Error'
                break
            if d[j] == ' ':
                ans = 'Error'
                break
        print(ans)
    else:
        print('Error')
